So I mean, do you think that, sorry, please go on.

20:03.640 --> 20:06.000
No, but as far as your question on,

20:07.040 --> 20:10.400
is there a stronger constituency for hate in the US

20:10.400 --> 20:12.640
or for Trump's sort of vitriolic appeals

20:12.640 --> 20:15.360
and for the Bernie appeals?

20:15.360 --> 20:18.000
I would say that when it comes to redistribution,

20:18.000 --> 20:19.520
yeah, it might be a watch.

20:19.520 --> 20:22.320
There might be a lot of half the country hoping

20:22.320 --> 20:25.120
for more redistribution in the abstract,

20:25.120 --> 20:29.600
half the country still bed into they're gonna strike it rich.

20:29.600 --> 20:32.320
So maybe let's hold off this redistribution stuff.

20:32.320 --> 20:35.800
I know I'm way behind on my mortgage and I'm in medical bed,

20:35.800 --> 20:40.120
but I'm one good move away from being wealthy.

20:40.120 --> 20:42.880
Of course, there's some aspect of that.

20:42.880 --> 20:45.640
When you compare America to, let's say Western Europe,

20:45.640 --> 20:47.560
I think you would find that Americans are,

20:47.560 --> 20:49.600
one, more welcoming of immigrants

20:49.600 --> 20:51.280
in a lot of countries in Western Europe.

20:51.280 --> 20:52.680
So Americans, for example,

20:52.680 --> 20:55.040
even a lot of people who vote for Trump,

20:55.040 --> 20:58.120
one, they vastly overestimate the amount of

20:59.120 --> 21:01.840
undocumented immigration the United States has,

21:01.840 --> 21:03.000
but more generally,

21:03.000 --> 21:07.600
therefore higher amounts of legal immigration

21:07.600 --> 21:11.280
and therefore tightening the border at the same time.

21:11.280 --> 21:13.040
So which is very different than some

21:13.040 --> 21:15.720
of these xenophobic appeals in Europe.

21:16.560 --> 21:18.360
A vast majority of Americans are for things

21:18.360 --> 21:19.680
like birthright citizenship.

21:19.680 --> 21:22.160
My parents came to the US in 1988.

21:22.160 --> 21:24.080
I was born in 1989.

21:24.200 --> 21:28.160
I would imagine that maybe not as commanding

21:28.160 --> 21:30.560
of a majority as it was in the past,

21:30.560 --> 21:33.680
but probably a majority of Republicans

21:33.680 --> 21:36.880
would agree that I have a right to be a US citizen.

21:36.880 --> 21:40.520
That's not the case in a lot of European countries.

21:41.560 --> 21:45.240
Most of those countries don't have birthright citizenship

21:45.240 --> 21:48.680
like we have throughout most of the Western hemisphere.

21:48.680 --> 21:49.880
On a host of other issues,

21:49.880 --> 21:53.400
I think you'll find that Americans as a whole,

21:53.400 --> 21:57.080
especially young people, hold more progressive views

21:57.080 --> 22:00.920
than their peers in the advanced capitalist world

22:00.920 --> 22:04.520
in Europe and even Japan, South Korea.

22:05.800 --> 22:10.120
This is a good starting point for us

22:10.120 --> 22:11.840
from progressive politics.

22:11.840 --> 22:14.320
And I think that we shouldn't let Trump's appeal

22:14.320 --> 22:17.760
maybe make us too pessimistic

22:17.760 --> 22:21.920
about where most Americans are on these issues.

